column5: Just back from Innisfil beach and checking the ice conditions for tomorrows Fishing for Tyler  Ice has firm up after the mild spell, ruts left in the slush out from  the ramp has firmed up, and may be a slight problem for snow vehicles little or NO snow cover on the ice, so it might be a bit slippery for the walkers. I did notice a few trucks and vans on the ice, a lot of huts further out  Cold temps overnight, clear evening sky, should set up well for tomorrow morning.  See you in the AM.  John
Glad to hear you are making it out ! See you in the morning. TB

I went down to the ice off the 8th  and found the same conditions  the parking lots are good, no one should get stuck...I mean me     <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://i25.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vid25.photobucket.com/albums/c52/Mrbeee1954/DIGI0001.flv">
Looking forward to seeing you John.

Was it just me? It didn't look like Terry was standing on the ice despite the fact that he said the ice was "fine".   The ice will be great, weather conditions look to be great, the people will be great and the fish  We shall see.
Just got home.. Ice is great.. just as others have said.. bring cleats, unless we get the snow they're calling for tonight, you may need them....  See you all tomorrow
